Geeker Chat Intro: Geek Chat is a GPT client that supports desktops, mobile phones, and tablets. It's easy to use with simple configuration for OpenAI's API or Azure OpenAI's API. Supported models include OpenAI models (such as gpt-3.5-turbo, gpt-3.5-turbo-16k, gpt-4, gpt-4-32k) and Google vertex-ai models (chat-bison, codechat-bison). Github: https://github.com/geeker-ai/geek_chat . Welcome to contribute!
buytips: GeekChat is a client that supports the currently popular large language models. It currently supports the OpenAI official API and the OpenAI models deployed on Azure. Users can choose to configure their own API access points or use GeekChat's default services. GeekChat aims to make it easy for everyone to use, and the model usage pricing is consistent with the official pricing. Learn more at: https://github.com/geeker-ai/geek_chat
Model name deployed on Azure: Deployment name and URL for the model deployed on Azure correspond to the EndPoint of the Azure resource.
model intro: Only when activated using the GeekChat service can the chat-bison and codechat-bison models be used normally.
